i have this div. i have 2 issues. a new line creates a div inside a div and i want to prevent that. 

<div class="text-input active" id="tb4-text-input-1" contenteditable="true" spellcheck="false" data-placeholder="Add Prompt Here">I make 6 cups of coffee&nbsp;<div>every night before I sleep. Today, my <span class="strikethrough-aed178">boyfriend</span> <span class="color-highlight-749ff7">cat</span> drank 2 cups of coffee while I was <span class="strikethrough-7994a0">sleeping.</span> <span class="color-highlight-3eeb27">sleeping at midnight.</span> How many cups of <span class="strikethrough-e7fa8c">coffee</span> <span class="color-highlight-34ef6a">drinks</span> will I look for when I wake up?</div></div>

and secondly. i am using  const prompt = document.getElementById("tb4-text-input-1").innerText; to get the content. how do i make it so that it does not include the content in spans that have strikethrough-* class. And I want to replace the content in class="collapsed-content" spans with the data-original-text property of the span.

<div class="text-input" id="tb4-text-input-1" contenteditable="true" spellcheck="false" data-placeholder="Add Prompt Here">I make 6 cups of coffee&nbsp;<div>every night before <span data-original-text="I sleep" class="collapsed-content" style="cursor: pointer;">...</span>. Today, my <span class="strikethrough-aed178">boyfriend</span> <span class="color-highlight-749ff7">cat</span> drank 2 cups of coffee while I was <span class="strikethrough-7994a0">sleeping.</span> <span class="color-highlight-3eeb27">sleeping at midnight.</span> How many cups of <span class="strikethrough-e7fa8c">coffee</span> <span class="color-highlight-34ef6a">drinks</span> will I look for when I wake up?</div></div>

*********

To prevent new lines from creating a div inside a div, you can add the following CSS rule to your stylesheet:

```css
.text-input > div {
  display: inline;
}
```

This will make the inner divs behave like inline elements, preventing them from creating new lines.

For the second issue, you can use the following JavaScript code to get the content without the strikethrough-* class and replace the content in class="collapsed-content" spans with the data-original-text property of the span:

```javascript
function getCleanText() {
  const textInput = document.getElementById("tb4-text-input-1");
  const clone = textInput.cloneNode(true);

  const strikethroughSpans = clone.querySelectorAll('[class^="strikethrough-"]');
  strikethroughSpans.forEach(span => span.remove());

  const collapsedContentSpans = clone.querySelectorAll('.collapsed-content');
  collapsedContentSpans.forEach(span => {
    const originalText = span.getAttribute('data-original-text');
    span.textContent = originalText;
  });

  return clone.innerText;
}

const prompt = getCleanText();
console.log(prompt);
```

This code first clones the text input element to avoid modifying the original content. Then, it removes all spans with a class starting with "strikethrough-". After that, it replaces the content of the "collapsed-content" spans with the data-original-text property. Finally, it returns the innerText of the modified clone.
